# Code Review Checklist

Use before marking any task complete.

## Architecture

- [ ] Change respects layer boundaries (route → service → provider/DB)
- [ ] No provider-specific logic leaked into routes or schemas
- [ ] Existing modules extended rather than duplicated
- [ ] Single `Base` metadata registry preserved

## Python / FastAPI

- [ ] Type hints on public functions and ORM fields
- [ ] Async used for I/O-bound operations
- [ ] Dependencies wired in `api/dependencies.py`
- [ ] Responses use `APIResponse[T]` envelope
- [ ] Errors use registered exception classes

## Database (if applicable)

- [ ] SQLAlchemy 2.x typed ORM style
- [ ] `TimestampMixin` used where audit columns are needed
- [ ] No table creation outside planned migration workflow
- [ ] Session lifecycle handled correctly (no leaked connections)

## Security (see `08-security.mdc`)

- [ ] No secrets in code or committed files
- [ ] Input validated via Pydantic schemas
- [ ] Error messages do not leak internal details

## Documentation (Definition of Done)

- [ ] `docs/PROJECT_MEMORY.md` updated
- [ ] `docs/CHANGELOG.md` updated
- [ ] `docs/ROADMAP.md` updated if phase changed
- [ ] `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` updated if structure changed
- [ ] ADR added if architectural decision made

## Known Issues to Watch

- Duplicate `get_llm_service()` in `dependencies.py`
- Duplicate `ChatResponse` in `schemas/chat.py`
- Stale `HealthResponse` stub in `schemas/common.py`
- `main.py` OpenAPI description still says "AI Coding Assistant"
- `LOG_LEVEL` setting unused in `core/logging.py`

Fix these when touching the affected files; do not expand scope unnecessarily.
